    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1863-09-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1863-09-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="195" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d195">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Clay</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 35.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1863-09-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 5, 1863.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> Your despatch of the 13th of August (No.
                            18) has been received, and the information it communicates, relating to
                            the events occurring in Poland, is appreciated.</p>
                <p>Your account of the character of the French note to Russia, and the
                            anticipated tone of the Austrian and British notes, accords, in all
                            respects, with the understanding that has obtained here on that
                            subject.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cassius</hi> M. <hi rend="smallcaps">Clay</hi>,
                                Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
